newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Profit-taking dampens Australian bond rally.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-Profit-taking dampens Australian bond rally.

text.p: *Profit-taking after the steep rally in Australian bonds that took yields to near 2-1/2 year lows on Wednesday kept the market on an offered bias through out the session.
Profit-taking after the steep rally in Australian bonds that took yields to near 2-1/2 year lows on Wednesday kept the market on an offered bias throughout the session, traders said.

However, stronger than expected business investment intentions contained in today's June quarter capital expenditure data failed to suggest the Reserve Bank will differ from what is seen as an easier bias in policy.
"Profit-taking seems to be from overseas, the domestic institutions seem to be reasonably happy at current levels," one trader added.
The weaker tone of the local market saw it give up some of Wednesday's spread tightening to other dollar bloc bonds. The market, however, remains close to the two-year spread lows against the U.S..
